# SeatingPlanPopover

## Summary

The one popover shell every planner popover shares: a themed surface with a sticky header (kicker/title or a custom `:header` block, always capped with a ✕ close button), a scrollable `:body` that limits its height so it never runs off-screen, and an optional pinned `:foot` for actions. It wraps the catalog `<Popover>` and owns sensible positioning defaults — kind 'edit', anchoring 'beside', placement 'right-start', elevation 'floating' — so most call sites only pass `@anchor` and `@onClose`. The planner uses it for table and fixture editors, tool panels, and centered, backdropped delete confirmations.

## Import

```js
import SeatingPlanPopover from '../components/seating-plan-popover';
```

## Template Usage

A centered confirmation, as used by the planner's delete flow:

```gjs
<SeatingPlanPopover
  @anchor='[data-tsp-root]'
  @onClose={{this.cancelDelete}}
  @kicker='Confirm'
  @title={{this.pendingDelete.title}}
  @kind='details'
  @anchoring='center'
  @backdrop='dim'
  @elevation='raised'
  @width={{320}}
>
  <:body>
    <p>{{this.pendingDelete.detail}}</p>
  </:body>
  <:foot>
    <button type='button' {{on 'click' this.confirmDelete}}>Delete</button>
  </:foot>
</SeatingPlanPopover>
```
